[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Deciding on setup factors**\n\nI need to figure out the setup needed beyond the scaffold. The current build uses add-opens in Gradle, which could be relevant for generated tests with native-run. I wonder if the driver scaffold should include existing tests for comprehensive coverage. There are concerns regarding Conscrypt needing JVM --add-opens for Java 9+ to access internals, and this seems important for the existing build.gradle. The user is asking if the library requires additional setup for better coverage. I need to research the documentation and dependencies further.\n\n**Exploring Gradle dependencies**\n\nI’m considering whether to use a Gradle dependency. The Conscrypt-openjdk-uber package seems to include natives without any transitive dependencies, and it’s noted in the POM file. I think I might need to fetch it using curl from Maven Central. I'll have to ensure I'm checking the right version and any required setup steps to use it properly. There's a lot to consider to get it right for the user!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d82d7a5f165c6b8016a42cebd53988194accf90ed46572167\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQs7Erpe4MEI2ffDBNclioAgVPwlV0GcfnXIxr0W9zQWduFi3WmcQ1wyyq8gJhhBwPkyOoWAJ58WhvAOIUK8ZJUnwVYERcnKj8J_0l5WeX9urjUNCZaaia5zMH8M2mFM7H4Cm8vztKkDprj1nKw8i8eulwNmcSd-MJgejM1_C-NYw1Jlsvcw_JZo0hB8MljJZav4aPt8m-vQ9Gcci-HDGsUbn3Ta6ag81dnRgTXFvypkjsyeoSUxvLATmIVVM58MXmAbvWfRm3NYyBiWLEQzXfZDTWyskLbU9hZ2wLmNoadMPK6ZdzLCBS-EWQP5yR5GmWKLd0KrwV-QG_-2HaARc_nFOyI6O3pG0EsUKKKCCHo6eXBDicErmJBI3oVSu07qBJ98BcZfs7itJwmOzxJfZ4SNf5X4WqvKJt-wM0WB59O6AGrwAEiJAI6X_lr-bNeal3dz5LAHQ8q5g-Cw7f5Yn-ujBa_cGUL_i3fTZ8SMOvJpPk3e6O8KpB3RuEpatsyH7AalFrODezJLKEMH17nGQHYEylfqkboZyxgjJhQ_rBcCL-J_HzN0tubP_QOfu90VmTgYCTtihf8ZllwkZLICHvDlS7IsaPqsXHi6T2ToEVo3IKY9Z7Ef7V142xG3GWTobnT_cIByC_8GBMQ8RhInJK2VHHrxQlJp2IpNSKELpKxXMYC_a6hk6qPCdCKE3sJeWk3di5