w7ePI19aBEPhpJhVXfTGl7PJo_I3RyQD6SBcC1_Qh3zCU9D0uw5KELTE5blhJxNhk0f0i_s_yW6k-9yDOYoMwiQsvecG-6uNGxp22TLTwxiQVpj4qxfBfkfwVEzuDL3U1uMCvdZWW-ytOjU0YOawtknPqCeptIGYv6g0GxPMzlW5Y6obT7w-hgTsiv7rhKQxm3LDbevnm6fz2M7pGjlMFJdf8LzkPoszFSB0oA-1PeAWzVz4WvbKmhGRgj15PbpW4s7Obpi7hzabAnQFpxioETEk10TdXJfr_oqEUVcQ4UcYFrIu1gvCoKhGe_fYjxV9aJDzc8\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native workdir issues**\\n\\nI'm analyzing whether to support the `org.conscrypt.native.workdir` setting if the temporary directory is marked as noexec. However, it seems unnecessary unless there are temp-related issues. I should also consider potential risks, such as module encapsulation in JDK 25 and the absence of certain APIs like TLSv1.3 in older versions. I’m thinking about validating existing tests and ensuring the produced JSON is concise and valid, possibly as a single object. I lean toward advisory preparation instead of immediate action.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed: the uber artifact has no POM dependencies and bundles the native Conscrypt libraries. Meaningful coverage does require JDK module-opening JVM/native-image arguments because Conscrypt 1.4.1 reflects into JDK internals.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure generated tests to pass the same module opens on JVM tests and native-image builds: --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED, --add-opens=java.base/java.net=ALL-UNNAMED, and --add-opens=java.base/sun.nio.ch=ALL-UNNAMED. Tests should explicitly initialize Conscrypt via Conscrypt.checkAvailability() and Conscrypt.newProvider(), and can exercise TLS/SSLEngine/socket behavior with loopback-only resources; no external server is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Conscrypt 1.4.1 predates strong JDK encapsulation and uses reflection on Socket, SocketImpl, SocketChannel, InetAddress, and ECParameterSpec internals; missing opens can make otherwise meaningful tests fail before metadata coverage is reached.\",\n    \"The artifact loads JNI libraries from META-INF/native, so native-image verification remains authoritative for resource/native-library metadata.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d82d7a5f165c6b8016a42cf1e55788194b110912baff938fa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2153, "output": 1253, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37198, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782763273947, "responseId": "resp_0d82d7a5f165c6b8016a42cf0a9ca081949433c55690d2502e"}, "toolResults": []}
